  "body": "The HTML [numeric character reference](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numeric_character_reference) / named character reference does not work for prop-values which is a common use case, e.g. for icons fonts (`data-icon=\"&#x1234;\"`).\n\nIt does work for raw strings in this fashion:\n\n``` html\n<i data-icon=\"&#xf00f;\" />\n```\n\nBut breaks in other scenarios:\n\n``` jsx\n<i data-icon={'&#x' + code + ';'} />\n<i data-icon={'\\u0026#x' + code + ';'} />\nReact.DOM.i( { 'data-icon': '&#x' + code + ';' } )\n```\n\nYielding:\n\n``` html\n<i data-icon=\"&amp;#x1234;\" />\n```\n\nThe only workaround I found so far is using dangerouslySetInnerHTML, which is a bit unfortunate as it forces me to introduce another wrapper for using a basic HTML feature.\n\n[JsFiddle sample](https://jsfiddle.net/69z2wepo/7284/)\n",
